cts {{harv|Gairdner|1925|p=26–27}}.}}  {{efn|name=h|{{IPA|/ħ/}} is realized as {{IPAblink|ħ}} or {{IPAblink|ʜ}}.}}  {{efn|name=ayn|{{IPA|/ʕ/}} is realized as {{IPAblink|ʕ}} or {{IPAblink|ʔˤ}} ({{harvnb|Al-Ani|2008|p=599}}; {{harvnb|Thelwall|Sa'adeddin|1999|p=51}}).}}  {{efn|name=ayn2|{{IPAslink|ʢ}} Neither pharyngeal nor fricative, but is more correctly described as a [[creaky_voice|creaky-voiced]] [[epiglottal_consonant|epiglottal]] [[approximant|approximant]] ({{Harvcoltxt|Ladefoged|Maddieson|1996|pp=167–168}}).}}  {{efn|name=Allah|{{IPA|[ɫ]}} only occurs in the word ''Allah'': {{IPA|[ɑɫˈɫɑh]}} ({{harvnb|Al-Ani|2008|p=600}}; {{harvnb|Kaye|1997|p=196}}).}}  {{efn|name=hamza|{{IPA|/ʔ/}} is usually written above or below three letters: {{lang|ar|أ}}, {{lang|ar|إ}}, {{lang|ar|آ}}, {{lang|ar|ئ}}, {{lang|ar|ؤ}}.}}  {{efn|name=a|Allophones of {{IPA|/a/}} include {{IPAblink|ɑ}} before emphatic consonants and {{IPAblink|q}}, {{IPAblink|r}} and {{IPAblink|æ}} elsewhere ({{harvnb|Al-Ani|2008|p=595, 600}}; {{harvnb|Thelwall|Sa'adeddin|1999|p=52–53}}; {{harvnb|Kaye|1997|p=193, 197}}).}}  {{efn|name=ɪ|Allophones of {{IPA|/ɪ/}} include {{IPAblink|i}}~{{IPAblink|e}} before emphatic consonants and {{IPAblink|q}}, {{IPAblink|r}}, {{IPAblink|ħ}}, {{IPAblink|ʕ}} ({{harvnb|Al-Ani|2008|p=595, 600}}; {{harvnb|Thelwall|Sa'adeddin|1999|p=52–53}}; {{harvnb|Kaye|1997|p=193, 197}}).}}  {{efn|name=u|Allophones of {{IPA|/u/}} include {{IPAblink|ʊ}}~{{IPAblink|ɤ}}~{{IPAblink|o}} before emphatic consonants and {{IPAblink|q}}, {{IPAblink|r}}, {{IPAblink|ħ}}, {{IPAblink|ʕ}} ({{harvnb|Al-Ani|2008|p=595, 600}}; {{harvnb|Thelwall|Sa'adeddin|1999|p=52–53}}; {{harvnb|Kaye|1997|p=193, 197}}).}}  {{efn|name=aa|Allophones of {{IPA|/aː/}} include {{IPAblink|ɑː}} before emphatic consonants and {{IPAblink|q}}, {{IPAblink|r}}; and {{IPAblink|æː}} elsewhere ({{harvnb|Al-Ani|2008|p=595, 600}}; {{harvnb|Thelwall|Sa'adeddin|1999|p=52–53}}; {{harvnb|Kaye|1997|p=193, 197}}).}}  {{efn|name=ii|Allophones of {{IPA|/iː